sing RSA Key Generation Concerns**\\n\\nI'm unsure about the small factor issue, so I’m considering using the encoded SubjectPublicKeyInfo from a Java-generated key and possibly replacing the algorithm ID. It seems like parsing the generated key's modulus could work, but I want to avoid setting risky system properties. Instead, using KeyPairGenerator should provide valid results without hardcoding values. I’m thinking about how to check if the non-default algorithm ID is preserved and if ASN1Null is acceptable in PSS parameters. I might need to add a provider for KeyFactory as well.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring BCRSAPublicKey Access**\\n\\nI'm realizing that the active BCRSAPublicKey constructors are inaccessible, so I have to rely on the public API, which requires a provider. Using a provider seems quite natural in this context. I'm considering whether I can directly use `org.bouncycastle.jcajce.provider.asymmetric.rsa.KeyFactorySpi`. It looks like the `generatePublic(SubjectPublicKeyInfo)` method is public, which might be a good way to access the functionality I need without running into issues.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_fUK7NOqB75I7WQ4Yuh0ts4I4|fc_0c26f0dd3a3c1da80169fbe176b4e88190ba71ab08950020ce", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15to18/1.77/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk15to18/BCRSAPublicKeyTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_bouncycastle.bcprov_jdk15to18;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectInputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;\nimport java.math.BigInteger;\nimport java.security.KeyFactory;\nimport java.security.KeyPair;\nimport java.security.KeyPairGenerator;\nimport java.security.Provider;\nimport java.security.interfaces.RSAPublicKey;\nimport java.security.spec.X509EncodedKeySpec;\n\nimport org.bouncycastle.asn1.ASN1Encoding;\nimport org.bouncycastle.asn1.DERNull;\nimport org.bouncycastle.asn1.pkcs.PKCSObjectIdentifiers;\nimport org.bouncycastle.asn1.x509.AlgorithmIdentifier;\nimport org.bouncycastle.asn1.x509.SubjectPublicKeyInfo;\nimport org.bouncycastle.jcajce.provider.asymmetric.rsa.BCRSAPublicKey;\nimport org.bouncycastle.jce.provider.BouncyCastleProvider;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class BCRSAPublicKeyTest {\n    private static final BigInteger PUBLIC_EXPONENT = BigInteger.valueOf(65537);\n\n    @Test\n    public void serializesAndDeserializesRsassaPssPublicKey() throws Exception {\n        BCRSAPublicKey publicKey = createRsassaPssPublicKey();\n\n        byte[] serializedKey = serialize(publicKey);\n        BCRSAPublicKey restoredKey = deserialize(serializedKey);\n\n        assertThat(restoredKey).isEqualTo(publicKey);\n        assertThat(restoredKey.hashCode()).isEqualTo(publicKey.hashCode());\n        assertThat(restoredKey.getAlgorithm()).isEqualTo(\"RSASSA-PSS\");\n        assertThat(restoredKey.getFormat()).isEqualTo(\"X.509\");\n        assertThat(restoredKey.getModulus()).isEqualTo(publicKey.getModulus());\n        assertThat(restoredKey.getPublicExponent()).isEqualTo(PUBLIC_EXPONENT);\n        assertThat(restoredKey.getEncoded()).isEqualTo(publicKey.getEncoded());\n    }\n\n    private static BCRSAPublicKey createRsassaPssPublicKey() throws Exception {\n        RSAPublicKey generatedKey = generateJdkRsaPublicKey();\n        org.bouncycastle.asn1.pkcs.RSAPublicKey rsaPublicKey = new org.bouncycastle.asn1.pkcs.RSAPublicKey(\n                generatedKey.getModulus(),\n                generatedKey.getPublicExponent());\n        AlgorithmIdentifier algorithmIdentifier = new AlgorithmIdentifier(\n                PKCSObjectIdentifiers.id_RSASSA_PSS,\n                DERNull.INSTANCE);\n        SubjectPublicKeyInfo publicKeyInfo = new SubjectPublicKeyInfo(algorithmIdentifier, rsaPublicKey);\n        Provider provider = new BouncyCastleProvider();\n        KeyFactory keyFactory = KeyFactory.getInstance(\"RSA\", provider);\n\n        Object publicKey = keyFactory.generatePublic(\n                new X509EncodedKeySpec(publicKeyInfo.getEncoded(ASN1Encoding.DER)));\n\n        assertThat(publicKey).isInstanceOf(BCRSAPublicKey.class);\n        return (BCRSAPublicKey) publicKey;\n    }\n\n    private static RSAPublicKey generateJdkRsaPublicKey() throws Exception {\n        KeyPairGenerator generator = KeyPairGenerator.getInstance(\"RSA\");\n        generator.initialize(512);\n        KeyPair keyPair = generator.generateKeyPair();\n        return (RSAPublicKey) keyPair.getPublic();\n    }\n\n    private static byte[] serialize(BCRSAPublicKey publicKey) throws Exception {\n        ByteArrayOutputStream bytes = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n        try (ObjectOutputStream out = new ObjectOutputStream(bytes)) {\n            out.writeObject(publicKey);\n        }\n        return bytes.toByteArray();\n    }\n\n    private static BCRSAPublicKey deserialize(byte[] serializedKey) throws Exception {\n        try (ObjectInputStream in = new ObjectInputStream(new ByteArrayInputStream(serializedKey))) {\n            return (BCRSAPublicKey) in.readObject();\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1400, "output": 1675, "cacheRead": 17920, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 20995, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778114915224, "responseId": "resp_0c26f0dd3a3c1da80169fbe163be088190812d9e34aa963dfb"}}
